The paper deals with compressed sensing, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also involves coding schemes, which falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper is motivated by networking applications, specifically identity tracking in an Internet-of-Things environment, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI) and networked systems (cs.NI).
